# Experience Catalogue (Sodexo Digital & AI Innovation)

Interactive catalogue of **90+** Sodexo digital solutions by areas (WORK / LEARN / HEAL / PLAY), personas, journey steps, and modules. **Content:** Notion. **Taxonomy source:** `Catalogue_XP_solutions.xlsx` ingested via `scripts/ingest-xp-catalogue-xlsx.py`.

## Assets policy (non-negotiable)

- **Local-only.** Every image, icon and asset ships in `public/images/catalogue/assets/`. **No remote image URLs, no Figma hotlinks, no third-party CDNs at runtime.** If a design is updated, export PNG/SVG locally and commit it.
- **No Figma references in shipped code.** Do not add `data-node-id`, `data-name`, Figma file keys, node IDs, or comments like "matches Figma" in TSX / TS / CSS that is bundled.
- Portrait paths live in `src/lib/data/personaPortraits.ts`; journey maps in `src/lib/data/personaJourneyConfig.ts`.

## Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS + CSS variables in `src/styles/tokens.css`
- **Fonts:** `next/font/google` (Fraunces display + Manrope body). Never re-add `@import url(fonts.googleapis.com)`.
- **Components:** Shadcn/ui base + catalogue-specific components
- **Icons:** `@phosphor-icons/react` only — **never emoji for UI icons**
- **State:** Zustand in `src/lib/store.ts` (favourites, filters, AI chat)
- **Data:** Notion via `src/lib/notion.ts`; fallback `src/lib/data/fallback.ts`; XP flow in `src/lib/data/xpCatalogueFlow.ts` merged by `xpFlowAdapter.ts`
- **Animation:** Framer Motion (page + card transitions)

## Architecture

- Fetch in **page.tsx** with `async/await` (server-side)
- Components are **presentational** — no direct Notion/API calls
- Types in `src/lib/data/types.ts`
- Notion: **`revalidate: 3600`** (1h ISR); use fallback if Notion fails

## Naming

- **PascalCase:** components, types
- **camelCase:** functions, variables, hooks
- **kebab-case:** route segments, CSS classes
- Hooks: **`use` prefix**

## Component pattern

```tsx
interface Props { solution: Solution; className?: string }
export function SolutionCard({ solution, className }: Props) {
  return <div className={cn("...", className)}>...</div>
}
```

Always: typed props, named export, Tailwind with token CSS vars via `cn()`.

## Building a screen

1. Map colours/spacing to token names from `src/styles/tokens.css` and `.impeccable.md`
2. Tailwind + CSS vars — never hard-code brand hex outside the token layer
3. Wrap sections in Framer Motion `motion.div` for entry animations (respect `prefers-reduced-motion`)
4. Every `<main>` must carry `id="main-content"` to pair with the global skip link

## Notion — Solutions DB (essential fields)

Title **Name**; Select: **Module**, **Type**, **Status**; Rich text: **Context**, **Description**, **KPIs** (JSON `[{v,l}]`), **Contact**, **Benefits_***; Multi-select: **Flags**, **Hashtags**, **Areas** (WORK/LEARN/HEAL/PLAY); URL **URL**; Rich text **Img** (emoji icon).

## Notion — Personas DB (essential fields)

Title **Name**; Select **Area**; Rich text: **FullName**, **Role**, **Quote**, **Motivations** / **Pains** / **Needs** (JSON arrays), **Steps**, **Color** (hex), **Emoji**; Files **Photo**.
